.isEnabled() - returns true, if button can be clicked
isSelected() -- returns true, if button already clicked
isDisplayed() -- returns true, if element is visible. Applies to any kind of webElement, not only radio buttons.

Note: if element doesn'' exist at all, you will get - NoSuchElementException.
This method will not work if element doesn't present in the HTML code. To verify if element is not in HTLM code at all,
use findElement().size() ==0;

driver.findElement()

<input type = "radio" id = "red" name = "color">

radioButton.getAttribute("id")   -- red

radioButton.getAttribute("type") -- radio

radioButton.getAttribute("id")   -- color
getText() -- nothing

Priority:
1. element must be present
2. element must be visible

